Hollywood's "Pokemon Detective Pikachu" continued to top the Chinese mainland box office Friday, according to the China Movie Data Information Network Saturday. The live-action/animated film grossed 23.40 million yuan (about 3.38 million US dollars) on the day. It was followed by Universal Picture's "A Dog's Journey", which took in about 18.86 million yuan in its first day on screen. Coming in the third was Disney and Marvel's "Avengers: Endgame," which took in about 11.32 million yuan. The fourth one was the Lebanese film "Capernaum," which earned around 5.58 million yuan. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starUnrealistic expectations thwart Chinese job recruitersDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los Angeles